- Minor Illusion worked on ANYTHING.  Enchanters disguised as the Felwithe castle, anyone?<br>
- EVERYONE learned to tailor their own patchwork armow<br>
- Haste items?  If you were extremely lucky, you might camp an FBSS for 3 days.<br>
- The Fanged Skull Stiletto (12/22, no stats) was the most fabled and godly weapon ever mentioned.<br>
- Dorn B'Dyn.  Enough said.<br>
- There were no h2h weapons, so monks used bare fists from 1-50.<br>
- A Werewolf in West Karana could keep people terrorized for hours.<br>
- Trumpy Tonics as a powerlevel tool.<br>
- Kithicor was the second newbie zone for Halflings<br>
- Hybrid HP was the same as warriors.<br>
- /shout Who has the Treant list?<br>
- A Flowing Black Robe was about the best a caster could expect until the planes.<br>
- Evil Erudites started in a hidden guild in Toxx forest.<br>
<br>
All I can think of for now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=serrikryuujin>SerrikRyuujin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/03 10:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4757.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darkinheritance.homestead.com/files/sigs/SerrikHead60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Old school</span><hr size=1> I remember<br>
<br>
-waiting lists for camps in befallen<br>
-waiting lists for camps in crushbone<br>
-waiting lists for every spire surrounding split paw<br>
<br>
....<br>
<br>
I greatly miss the challenge traveling used to be.  To me the POK travel system changed the feel of the game for newer characters more then anything else.  It trivialised life in general for the younger characters.<br>
<br>
While making life easier, I feel it robs us all of some challenge and in the challenges lie the adventures. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
