<br>
So I remember killing Loathsome Individuals in the Qeynos Hills.  I wasn't aware these were tied to Rubicite armor, of which I had seen an entire suit.  A guy running around in all-red armor was quite noticeable in those days.<br>
<br>
I remember deep waiting lists for camps in South Karana.  Treants, hermit, etc.  Over 80 players in that zone on any given night.  Same with Oasis.  Lockjaw was a free-for-all gang up and kill the bastard fight.<br>
<br>
I used to make good money with my druid in the teleporting business.  I make 600pp once to port 3 dead folks out to Iceclad.  Tower of Frozen Shadows!  eeep!<br>
<br>
Having to sit around auctioning off your huge collection of worthless garbage in North Freeport.  I always, always hated that.  It was the biggest waste of a Saturday afternoon, but it had to be done.  Somewhere, somebody really wanted that Green Silken Drape.  It was just a matter of auctioning enough times until they heard you.....<br>
<br>
Bazaar was the best idea they have ever come up with.  I might be old school, but I am flexible, and I really like a lot of the changes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zhillan>Zhillan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/03 3:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4757.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.zoominternet.net/~noctem/zhillan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Old school</span><hr size=1> *laughing and shaking my head*<br>
